---
import DoorArch from './DoorArch.astro';
// "How we got here" — the origin story, conversational, SA-flavoured.
// Two voices: the softy asking, the penguin community replying.
---

<section id="backstory" class="py-24 sm:py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
  {/* Ambient warmth */}
  <div aria-hidden="true" class="soft-orb animate-float-slow" style="width: 440px; height: 440px; top: 80px; right: -60px; background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(247, 212, 192, 0.55), transparent 60%);"></div>
  <div aria-hidden="true" class="soft-orb animate-float-slower" style="width: 360px; height: 360px; bottom: -80px; left: -80px; background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(232, 154, 43, 0.14), transparent 60%); animation-delay: -7s;"></div>

  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8 relative">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm font-mono text-ink-500 mb-6">
      <span>05</span>
      <span class="w-8 h-px bg-padkos-light opacity-60"></span>
      <span class="tracking-widest uppercase text-xs">How we got here</span>
    </div>

    <h2 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl leading-[1.02] tracking-tight mb-4 max-w-3xl">
      So how did we get here?
    </h2>
    <p class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl italic text-padkos mb-16 max-w-2xl leading-snug">
      A backstory, as requested.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-8 items-start">

      {/* VOICE 1 — the ask, left side */}
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-7 md:col-start-1">
        <div class="soft-card p-7 md:p-9 relative">
          {/* A little "message" tail */}
          <span aria-hidden="true" class="hidden md:block absolute -bottom-3 left-10 w-6 h-6 bg-cream-50 border-r border-b border-cream-300 rotate-45"></span>

          <div class="chip mb-5">
            <span class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-hearty"></span>
            A softy, shouting into penguin land
          </div>

          <p class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl italic leading-snug text-ink-900 mb-4">
            "Sooo I couldn't figure out how the <span class="text-padkos">Linux thingy magicky</span> work, so I tuned it…"
          </p>
          <p class="font-display text-lg md:text-xl italic leading-snug text-ink-700 mb-4">
            "Hey my <span class="text-padkos">bru, howzit</span> in penguin land?"
          </p>
          <p class="font-display text-lg md:text-xl italic leading-snug text-ink-700">
            "Care to make it easy for a <span class="text-padkos">beeeg softy</span> like me that can't get his nerd on?"
          </p>

          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-500">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-hearty/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-hearty"></span>
            </span>
            Asked awkwardly. Meant it.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* The pause between voices */}
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-12 text-center my-4 md:my-2 order-3 md:order-none">
        <DoorArch variant="divider" class="mx-auto w-44 h-10 text-padkos opacity-60" />
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-500 mt-2 text-sm md:text-base">
          The penguins — warm, patient, unbothered — replied:
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* VOICE 2 — the reply, right side, dark */}
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-7 md:col-start-6 order-4 md:order-none">
        <div class="bg-ink-900 text-cream-100 rounded-softer p-7 md:p-9 shadow-puff-lg relative">
          <span aria-hidden="true" class="hidden md:block absolute -top-3 right-10 w-6 h-6 bg-ink-900 rotate-45"></span>

          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full bg-saffron-light text-ink-900 font-mono text-[0.72rem] uppercase tracking-widest border border-saffron mb-5">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-ink-900"></span>
            The penguins, replying
          </div>

          <p class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl italic leading-snug text-cream-50 mb-4">
            "Sure, <span class="text-saffron">boet.</span> Try this one — atomic, doesn't break, works like a regular computer."
          </p>
          <p class="font-display text-lg md:text-xl italic leading-snug text-cream-200 mb-4">
            "Updates swap, rollbacks roll back, Steam just runs. Hand it to your mom. Hand it to your cousin. Hand it to the mate who swore off computers after the last <span class="text-saffron">‘upgrade.'</span>"
          </p>

          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-cream-200/60">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-saffron/25 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-saffron"></span>
            </span>
            Answered kindly. Meant it too.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* The narrative conclusion */}
    <div class="mt-16 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        And it was…&nbsp;<span class="italic font-display text-padkos">fine?</span> Better than fine. Updates didn't break it. Rollbacks actually worked. Family laptops didn't need WhatsApp support sessions every second weekend. Tjops stayed on the <span class="italic">braai</span>, not on fire.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        So we started handing it to everyone. Mom's Thinkpad. The cousin's gaming rig. The mate who swore off computers. They all went <span class="italic font-display text-padkos">"oh. This is just… easier?"</span>
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">
        And we realised: the hardest part of Linux was <span class="italic font-display">picking which Linux.</span> So we made one pick, one opinion, four flavors, and removed the rest.
      </p>

      <p class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl italic text-ink-900 leading-snug">
        That's Macrosofty. A <span class="text-padkos">love letter</span> from one softy to another — with a door where there used to be a wall.
      </p>
    </div>

    {/* Sign-off strip */}
    <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-cream-300 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-4">
      <p class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-500 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-padkos" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M 3 12 Q 5 8 8 8 T 13 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none"/>
          <circle cx="8" cy="4" r="2" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.3"/>
        </svg>
        Written at a braai &middot; sometime in 2026 &middot; probably over tjops
      </p>
      <span class="chip" style="background: theme('colors.ink.900'); color: theme('colors.cream.50'); border-color: theme('colors.ink.900');">
        Peace, not war
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
